					<div id=3D"contentSub"><div id=3D"mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
				=09
				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Con=
cept in modular arithmetic</div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathem=
atics">mathematics</a>, particularly in the area of <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic" title=3D"Arithmetic">arithmetic</a>, a <b>mod=
ular multiplicative inverse</b> of an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Integer" title=3D"Integer">integer</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> is an integer <span class=3D"texhtml mva=
r" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> such that the product <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">ax</span> is <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congruence_relation#Basic_example" title=3D"Congr=
uence relation">congruent</a> to 1 with respect to the modulus <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-Rosen132_1-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Modular_multiplicative_inverse#cite_note-Rosen132-1"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In the sta=
ndard notation of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_arithmet=
ic" title=3D"Modular arithmetic">modular arithmetic</a> this congruence is =
written as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ax\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax\equiv 1{\p=
mod {m}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6d14ffceac68514b13b3d2fd87b9febab0d27766" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:19.192ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>which is the shorthand way of writing the statement that <span class=3D"=
