<p>Unlike linear equations over the reals, linear congruences may have zero=
, one or several solutions. If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-s=
tyle:italic;">x</span> is a solution of a linear congruence then every elem=
ent in <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 {\overline {x}}}">
