_of_integers_modulo_n" title=3D"Multiplicative group of integers modulo n">=
Multiplicative group of integers modulo n</a></div>
<p>Not every element of a complete residue system modulo <span class=3D"tex=
html mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> has a modular multiplicati=
ve inverse, for instance, zero never does. After removing the elements of a=
 complete residue system that are not relatively prime to <span class=3D"te=
xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, what is left is called a=
 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reduced_residue_system" title=
=3D"Reduced residue system">reduced residue system</a></b>, all of whose el=
ements have modular multiplicative inverses. The number of elements in a re=
duced residue system is <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-in=
line"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"=
display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=
=3D"{\displaystyle \phi (m)}">
