        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo movablelimits=3D"true" form=3D"prefix">gcd</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>1.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax+my=3D\gcd(=
a,m)=3D1.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/656aebc88458ed2f2bab56a436ca8ecb9532dabd" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:26.203ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
+my=3D\gcd(a,m)=3D1.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Rewritten, this is
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ax-1=3D(-y)m,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax-1=3D(-y)m,=
}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2c12481175ddb4e4fb0a407b0610b4d571eb6af8" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:17.121ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
-1=3D(-y)m,}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>that is,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ax\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax\equiv 1{\p=
mod {m}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6d14ffceac68514b13b3d2fd87b9febab0d27766" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:19.192ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>so, a modular multiplicative inverse of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> has been calculated. A more efficient ve=
rsion of the algorithm is the extended Euclidean algorithm, which, by using=
 auxiliary equations, reduces two passes through the algorithm (back substi=
tution can be thought of as passing through the algorithm in reverse) to ju=
st one.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Big_O_notation" title=3D=
"Big O notation">big O notation</a>, this algorithm runs in time <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml">O(log<sup>2</sup>(<i>m</i>))</span>, assuming <span class=3D"=
texhtml">|<span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em; padding-right=
:0.1em;"><i>a</i></span>| &lt; <i>m</i></span>, and is considered to be ver=
y fast and generally more efficient than its alternative, exponentiation.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Using_Euler's_theorem"><spa=
n id=3D"Using_Euler.27s_theorem"></span>Using Euler's theorem</h3><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModular_multiplicative_in=
verse&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Using Euler=
's theorem"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</=
span></span></div>
<p>As an alternative to the extended Euclidean algorithm, Euler's theorem m=
ay be used to compute modular inverses.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_multiplicative_inv=
erse#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>According to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler%27s_theo=
rem" title=3D"Euler's theorem">Euler's theorem</a>, if <span class=3D"texht=
ml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> is <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Coprime" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Coprime">coprime</a=
> to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, th=
at is, <span class=3D"texhtml">gcd(<i>a</i>, <i>m</i>) =3D 1</span>, then
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e a^{\phi (m)}\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
            <mi>m</mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a^{\phi (m)}\=
equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/5224c3ba00b60cd7a8c3b5fc19e1308fa309dbcd" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:21.796ex; height:3.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a^=
{\phi (m)}\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le \phi }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi }</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/72b1f30316670aee6270a28334bdf4f5072cdde4" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:1.385ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ph=
i }"></span> is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler%27s_totient_=
function" title=3D"Euler's totient function">Euler's totient function</a>. =
This follows from the fact that <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-=
style:italic;">a</span> belongs to the multiplicative group <span class=3D"=
mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-in=
line mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://w=
ww.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle (\mathbb {Z} /m\mathb=
b {Z} )}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"double-struck">Z</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"double-struck">Z</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle (\mathbb {Z} =
/m\mathbb {Z} )}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8346630a344336b9080498fcdcb1648b2181aa5a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:8.113ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle (\m=
athbb {Z} /m\mathbb {Z} )}"></span><sup>=C3=97</sup> <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/If_and_only_if" title=3D"If and only if">if and only if<=
/a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> is <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coprime" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Coprime">coprime</a> to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">m</span>. Therefore, a modular multiplicative inverse can be fo=
und directly:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e a^{\phi (m)-1}\equiv a^{-1}{\pmod {m}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
            <mi>m</mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a^{\phi (m)-1=
}\equiv a^{-1}{\pmod {m}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/91f6249ebf002b7c8d40e294da74a899096198ae" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:26.297ex; height:3.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a^=
{\phi (m)-1}\equiv a^{-1}{\pmod {m}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>In the special case where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">m</span> is a prime, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-e=
lement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" =
style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"=
 alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \phi (m)=3Dm-1}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi (m)=3Dm-=
1}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3d2dafad96506fb9510423a8aae20a9d784ca887" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:14.377ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \p=
hi (m)=3Dm-1}"></span> and a modular inverse is given by=20
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e a^{-1}\equiv a^{m-2}{\pmod {m}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>m</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a^{-1}\equiv =
a^{m-2}{\pmod {m}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fc1ce1ba0e6bb5fcdc65bca712a7d741668dd789" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:24.038ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a^=
{-1}\equiv a^{m-2}{\pmod {m}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>This method is generally slower than the extended Euclidean algorithm, b=
ut is sometimes used when an implementation for modular exponentiation is a=
lready available. Some disadvantages of this method include:
</p>
<ul><li>The value <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline">=
<span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"displa=
y: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \phi (m)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi (m)}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/52ddd8905bfc0ea59762651f0d18b1ec147006c2" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:5.235ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ph=
i (m)}"></span> must be known and the most efficient known computation requ=
ires <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>'s <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorization" title=3D"Factorizati=
on">factorization</a>. Factorization is widely believed to be a computation=
ally hard problem.  However, calculating <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mw=
e-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathm=
l-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math=
/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \phi (m)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=95<!-- =CF=95 --></mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi (m)}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/52ddd8905bfc0ea59762651f0d18b1ec147006c2" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:5.235ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ph=
i (m)}"></span> is straightforward when the prime factorization of <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> is known.</li>
<li>The relative cost of exponentiation. Though it can be implemented more =
efficiently using <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_exponent=
iation" title=3D"Modular exponentiation">modular exponentiation</a>, when l=
arge values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m<=
/span> are involved this is most efficiently computed with the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montgomery_reduction" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Montgomery reduction">Montgomery reduction</a> method, that method, =
itself, requiring a modular inverse mod <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, which is what was to be calculated in the=
 first place. Without the Montgomery method, the standard <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_exponentiation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Binary exponentiation">binary exponentiation</a>, which requires divisi=
on mod <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> a=
t every step, is a slow operation when <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> is large.</li></ul>
<p>One notable <i>advantage</i> of this technique is that there are no cond=
itional branches which depend on the value of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span>, and thus the value of <span class=3D=
"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span>, which may be an impor=
tant secret in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public-key_cryptogr=
aphy" title=3D"Public-key cryptography">public-key cryptography</a>, can be=
 protected from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Side-channel_attac=
k" title=3D"Side-channel attack">side-channel attacks</a>.  For this reason=
, the standard implementation of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
urve25519" title=3D"Curve25519">Curve25519</a> uses this technique to compu=
te an inverse.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Multiple_inverses">Multiple=
 inverses</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMo=
dular_multiplicative_inverse&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Ed=
it section: Multiple inverses"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>It is possible to compute the inverse of multiple numbers <span class=3D=
"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a<sub>i</sub></span>, modulo a =
common <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, =
with a single invocation of the Euclidean algorithm and three multiplicatio=
ns per additional input.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_multiplicative_inverse#cite_note-=
12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>  The basic idea is to form the product of all the <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a<sub>i</sub></span>, inve=
rt that, then multiply by <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">a<sub>j</sub></span> for all <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>j</i> =E2=
=89=A0 <i>i</i></span> to leave only the desired <span class=3D"texhtml"><i=
>a</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"display:inline-block;margin-bot=
tom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align=
:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:b=
aseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:in=
herit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>i</i></sub></span></span></span>.
</p><p>More specifically, the algorithm is (all arithmetic performed modulo=
 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>):
</p>
<ol><li>Compute the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prefix_sum" ti=
tle=3D"Prefix sum">prefix products</a> <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-=
math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-=
a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/M=
athML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle b_{i}=3D\prod _{j=3D1}^{i}a_{j}=3Da_{i}b_{i-1=
}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=8F<!-- =E2=88=8F --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>j</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>j</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <msub>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle b_{i}=3D\prod _{=
j=3D1}^{i}a_{j}=3Da_{i}b_{i-1}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3a1921af90ac09c398872a698ae82149ede48b21" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:21.652ex; height:3.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle b_{i}=
=3D\prod _{j=3D1}^{i}a_{j}=3Da_{i}b_{i-1}}"></span> for all <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><i>i</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>n</i></span>.</li>
<li>Compute <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span st=
yle=3D"display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line=
-height:1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inheri=
t;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub sty=
le=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>n</=
i></sub></span></span></span> using any available algorithm.</li>
<li>For <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">i</span> =
from <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> dow=
n to 2, compute
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=
=3D"display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-he=
ight:1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;l=
ine-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=
=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>i</i>=
</sub></span></span> =3D <i>b</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"disp=
lay:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1.2=
em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-heig=
ht:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=3D"font-=
size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>i</i></sub></s=
pan></span><i>b</i><sub><i>i</i>=E2=88=921</sub></span> and</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"d=
isplay:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:=
1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-h=
eight:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=3D"fo=
nt-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>i</i>=E2=88=
=921</sub></span></span> =3D <i>b</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"=
display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height=
:1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-=
height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=3D"f=
ont-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"><i>i</i></sub=
></span></span><i>a<sub>i</sub></i></span>.</li></ul></li>
<li>Finally, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span s=
tyle=3D"display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;lin=
e-height:1.2em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inher=
it;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub st=
yle=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">1</su=
b></span></span> =3D <i>b</i><span class=3D"nowrap"><span style=3D"display:=
inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:-0.4em;line-height:1.2em;f=
ont-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:i=
nherit;vertical-align:baseline">=E2=88=921</sup><br><sub style=3D"font-size=
:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">1</sub></span></span>=
</span>.</li></ol>
<p>It is possible to perform the multiplications in a tree structure rather=
 than linearly to exploit <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parallel=
_computing" title=3D"Parallel computing">parallel computing</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Inverses_modulo_prime_power=
s_(including_powers_of_2)"><span id=3D"Inverses_modulo_prime_powers_.28incl=
uding_powers_of_2.29"></span>Inverses modulo prime powers (including powers=
 of 2)</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
cket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModul=
ar_multiplicative_inverse&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit =
section: Inverses modulo prime powers (including powers of 2)"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the case where the modulus <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">m</span> is on the form <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe=
-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml=
-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/=
MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle p^{m}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>m</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p^{m}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3bab32900e0cbcdf2743e43f83431e87e56c734e" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:2.934ex; height:2.676ex;" al=
t=3D"{\displaystyle p^{m}}"></span> for some prime number <span class=3D"te=
xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span> and positive integer <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>, it is possi=
ble to compute modular multiplicative inverses efficiently by using the New=
ton-Raphson iteration, allowing the inverse to be computed with <span class=
=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathm=
l-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http=
://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle O(\log m)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>O</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>log</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle O(\log m)}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/01cc8bc56e37299e3f7da69f923f11e601030fd6" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:8.982ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle O(\=
log m)}"></span> multiplications. It can be shown that if
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ax\equiv 1{\pmod {p^{k}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <msup>
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>k</mi>
            </mrow>
          </msup>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax\equiv 1{\p=
mod {p^{k}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f2192cce04f19651bc4071994fb32d1483eda4cf" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:18.763ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
\equiv 1{\pmod {p^{k}}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>(that is, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</s=
pan> is a modular multiplicative inverse of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> modulo <span class=3D"mwe-math-element =
mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mat=
hml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Ma=
th/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle p^{k}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p^{k}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e017c102135ab13bdf501dc1c1b5fd1840a97822" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:2.348ex; height:3.009ex;" al=
t=3D"{\displaystyle p^{k}}"></span>), then
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ax\left(2-ax\right)\equiv 1{\pmod {p^{2k}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mn>2</mn>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>a</mi>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=89=A1<!-- =E2=89=A1 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width=3D"0.333em"></mspace>
          <msup>
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>k</mi>
            </mrow>
          </msup>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax\left(2-ax\=
right)\equiv 1{\pmod {p^{2k}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/45c5b49081ec641e685cc10bbc37c66eca57d793" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:28.343ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ax=
\left(2-ax\right)\equiv 1{\pmod {p^{2k}}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>which means that it is possible to perform a modulo calculation by first=
 computing a modular multiplicative inverse of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar"=
 style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> modulo the prime number <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span> or a small power th=
ereof, then performing a series of Newton-Raphson iterations to compute the=
 inverse modulo progressively larger prime powers <span class=3D"mwe-math-e=
lement mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-m=
ath-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/=
1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle p^{2^{n}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msup>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>n</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p^{2^{n}}}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/bd959c59eba9f2c99c2e5fd0c0f9af9f84790b71" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:3.278ex; height:3.009ex;" al=
t=3D"{\displaystyle p^{2^{n}}}"></span> for progressively larger values of =
<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Modular_multiplicative_inverse#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modula=
r_multiplicative_inverse#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div style=3D"width:100%; height:1em; clear:both;"></div>
<p>A practical use of this method is to efficiently compute modular multipl=
icative inverses modulo powers of 2. For such a calculation, one could star=
t with noting that all odd integers are their own modular multiplicative in=
verses modulo <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><spa=
n class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: n=
one;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displ=
aystyle 2^{3}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2^{3}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/52e9f8299773e9205d2055998f3c8eb9441877fc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:2.217ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2^{=
3}}"></span>, as can be shown by inspection:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 1*1=3D1\equiv 1{\pmod {8}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
